Let us work through the details for both IIA discrete torsion,
as well as the other degrees of freedom discussed in this paper.

Recall ordinary discrete torsion, viewed as an orbifold group action
on the  field, is defined by taking the bundles with connection
to be trivial, with gauge-trivial connection; discrete torsion is encoded
in the connection-preserving bundle isomorphisms that preserve the group law.
In terms of the  field data above, if we take the 1-gerbes to be
trivial, with gauge-trivial connection, then the maps 

