Thus, we have duplicated IIA discrete torsion as an unusual action
on the M theory  field.


The reader might well ask, what is the M theory dual of the other
IIA degrees of freedom discussed in this paper?
This question is also straightforward to answer.
Recall that for toroidal orbifolds, these other degrees of freedom
were described by trivial bundles  with flat nonzero connections
