Consistency check:  twisted sector phases from wrapped
membranes 


Although the statements above both seem straightforward,
we shall check both statements by computing phase factors from
membranes on  twisted sectors.  In particular, if we wrap
a membrane on the eleven-dimensional circle, we should recover a IIA string.
In this manner, we will be able to explicitly recover the usual
IIA twisted sector phase factors from membrane phase factors due
to the  field.

 
